---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const rawBaseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const baseUrl = rawBaseUrl.endsWith('/') ? rawBaseUrl : `${rawBaseUrl}/`;
---

<Layout title="Notes - Binh Pham">
  <h1>Notes</h1>
  <p>Debugging notes, implementation logs, and things I learned while writing firmware.</p>

  <section class="note-entry">
    <a href={`${baseUrl}blog/self-balancing-electric-motorcycle-paper/`}>
      <h2>Study and Implementation of Self-Balancing Electric Motorcycle</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="note-desc">A compact research note on the reaction-wheel model, Kalman-filtered MPU6050 angle estimate, PID/LQR comparison, and physical prototype validation.</p>
    <div class="note-tags">
      <span>Control</span>
      <span>LQR</span>
      <span>IMU</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="note-entry">
    <a href={`${baseUrl}blog/calibrating-loadcells/`}>
      <h2>Calibrating Loadcells: Digital Noise Filtering in Embedded C</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="note-desc">Tare calibration, moving average, and 1D Kalman filter implementation on Cortex-M for stable weight readings.</p>
    <div class="note-tags">
      <span>Sensors</span>
      <span>ADC</span>
      <span>Filtering</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="note-entry">
    <a href={`${baseUrl}blog/pdm-vs-pcm/`}>
      <h2>PDM vs PCM in Embedded Audio</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="note-desc">Quick reference on what PDM and PCM are, and how they relate in embedded audio capture.</p>
    <div class="note-tags">
      <span>Audio</span>
      <span>PDM</span>
      <span>PCM</span>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .note-entry {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .note-entry h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .note-desc {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }

  .note-tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .note-tags span {
    font: 400 0.67rem 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    padding: 0.17rem 0.48rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
